    "Body": " About Us Tassat Group LLC, is a New York-based fintech company that provides blockchain-based technology solutions for Digital Payments and Digital Asset Derivative markets.?? Tassat has already delivered the first digital payments platform approved by the NYDFS that has transacted significant volume to date, and plans to launch a CFTC-regulated digital asset derivatives exchange designed for institutional investors. All products listed for trading on the exchange will be self-certified with the CFTC???? ?? Our digital asset ecosystem also offers data analytics products, including a comprehensive benchmark for Bitcoin and Ether. ?? You can find us in the vibrant Flatiron District. As an Operations and Risk Specialist, you will be responsible for daily operational processes within the Prime Brokerage business of the Tassat Swap Dealer. Additionally, you will be responsible for monitoring and mitigating credit and market risk of the Prime Brokerage business as a whole, as well as risk of each customer. Working With Us At Tassat, you will work with incredibly talented engineers, market experts, and thought leaders to shape the future of a financial ecosystem. We offer a uniquely entrepreneurial, supportive culture, where ideas can come from anywhere and execution is everything. We understand the importance of autonomy, mastery, and purpose We strive to be extremely transparent, organizationally flat, and open-minded. While you will have clearly delineated responsibilities, you are welcome and encouraged to contribute beyond those areas. We value ideas and results, not ranks and titles We believe great results can only come from great people. If you're interested in working alongside people who are bright, creative, and diligent, this is the place Who We're Looking For Operations and Risk Specialist Opportunity We value people who can bring new perspectives to our company. Here are some traits that are important to us: Ability to solve problems head on (and hands-on) and in simple creative ways Bring unwavering passion to the team and the work you do Reliable and independent. We expect a lot out of you, but we won't keep tabs on you. You must thrive in that kind of environment Savvy researcher, continuous learner, and enthusiastic team player. We need you to feel like an owner, motivated to succeed and enthusiastic about helping others Urgency is key! We all play many roles here and must get our hands into everything to get it done What You Own Perform all daily prime brokerage operational flows including margin processing, settlement processing, close-of-market flows, and customer position / credit limits Monitor credit and market risk of the Prime Brokerage operation Work with clients who are delinquent in either margin posting or settlement funding in order to \u201ccure\u201d such delinquencies within the defined cure period Working with Tassat\u2019s margin and risk management models and frameworks to minimize / mitigate credit and market risk Working closely with and serving as a backup member of the Default Management Team to protect Tassat in cases of customer default and / or delivery failure Working with the quant department to perform periodic margin model calibration, stress testing, and back-testing What You Bring A solid understanding of financial markets operations, with a particular emphasis on derivatives A core understanding of the mechanics of derivative products such as forwards and options A broad knowledge of market structure, cleared and uncleared derivative processes and workflows An understanding of the credit and market risk inherent in bilateral derivatives trading Experience with margin models and / or the ability to learn and understand such models to a high degree The ability to work professionally with clients in the very stressful situations of margin and settlement delinquencies The ability to work calmly in the face of very stressful default situations in order to prevent / minimize losses for Tassat You Should Have 5-7 years experience in an operations, risk, trading or product related role at a derivatives exchange, derivatives dealer, broker/dealer or clearing house Very strong excel skills The ability to learn and understand core risk mathematical models such as margin models and optimization schemes A high comfort level working under stress and time pressure Knowledge in digital assets would be a plus Tassat Group LLC is an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. ", 
